# Docker build-context excludes for the production api + web images
# (ADR-0014 §7). Both Dockerfiles build with the repo root as context, so this
# single file governs both. The goal: ship only source + manifests into the
# build, never host-side installs, build outputs, or secrets.

# Git metadata
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Dependencies — reinstalled inside the image from the committed lockfile
**/node_modules

# Build outputs — rebuilt inside the image
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Secrets / environment files — NEVER copy into an image (ADR-0013 Tier 1/2).
# The committed `*.example` templates are safe and re-included below.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/*.example

# Test / coverage / logs / caches
**/coverage
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# The driver mobile app is a standalone Expo project (ADR-0033), not part of
# the api/web server images.
apps-mobile

# Operator orchestration-loop runtime (scripts/orchestration/) — not shipped.
scripts/orchestration/state.json
scripts/orchestration/logs
scripts/orchestration/decisions.log
scripts/orchestration/.stop
scripts/orchestration/.env
scripts/orchestration/dist
scripts/orchestration/node_modules

# Docker + CI files themselves do not belong inside the image
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
.github
